Grafting Instructions for Rogue Hood
written by PumpkinMama from
http://pumpkinknits.blogspot.com

Instructions written for grafting with right side of hood on front needle and left side on back needle (i.e. hood opening for face is on your right)

Abbreviations:  

F#= front needle stitch (numbers refer to the 38 live stitches remaining after completing hood as in step #20, beginning with 3 stitch stockinette border)
B#= back needle stitch
KOFF= pass yarn through Knitwise and pull stitch off needle
POFF= pass yarn through purlwise and pull stitch of needle
K= pass yarn knitwise and leave stitch on needle
P= pass yarn purlwise and leave stitch on needle

Use "chart" below as follows: follow instructions for passing yarn for 1st two stitches on front needles, then 1st two stitches on back needle, then do 2 more off front needles as written and 2 more off back needles as written.

remember to stop and snug up your grafted seam every 4-5 stitches or so....


F1 K		B1 P

F1 KOFF		B1 POFF
F2 P		B2 K

F2 KOFF		B2 POFF
F3 P		B3 K

F3 KOFF		B3 POFF
F4 K		B4 P

F4 POFF		B4 KOFF
